berdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeen, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","France":"Frankrijk","Aberdeen, Aberdeenshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni":"Aberdeen, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1162–1205":"1162–1205","1160–1206":"1160–1206","1184–1238":"1184–1238","1190–1252":"1190–1252","–1164":"–1164","–1202":"–1202","–1214":"–1214","–1233":"–1233","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1138–1162":"1138–1162","1125–Female":"1125–Deceased","1190":"1190","1164":"1164","1252":"1252","1162":"1162","1184":"1184","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","alive 1164":"1164","1205":"1205","1238":"1238","1138":"1138","1214":"1214","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1233":"1233","after 1202":"after 1202","Picardy, France":"Picardie, France","Aberdeen, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeen, Scotland, United Kingdom","France":"France","Aberdeen, Aberdeenshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni":"Aberdeen, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Fontaines","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Andre, Normand, Pierre, Emile, Fernand, Lucien, Marcel, Adelard, Henri, Jacques, Laurent.","French and Walloon: topographic name for someone living near a spring or well, from Old French <i>fontaine</i>, from Late Latin <i>fontana</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>fons</i> (see   Font  ); or a habitational name from Fontaine, the name of several places in various parts of France. Compare   Fountaine  .","Shortened form of French   Lafontaine  , a variant of 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Fontenot","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Ulysse, Andrus, Alcide, Andre, Edouard, Lucien, Marise, Monique, Remy.","French: variant of <b>Fonteneau</b> (and, in North America, an altered form of this), a topographic name from a diminutive of Old French <i>fontaine</i> ‘spring, well’ (see   Fontaine  ), or a habitational name from any of several places mainly in the westcentral part of France so named. The surname <i>Fontenot</i> is very rare in France.","History: Jean-Louis Fonteneau/Fontenot from Montierneuf in Vienne, France, married Louise-Angélique Henry in Mobile, AL, in 1726."]},{"name":"Fontenelle","meanings":["French: topographic name from a diminutive of Old French <i>fontaine</i> ‘spring, well’ (see   Fontaine  ), or a habitational name from (La) Fontenelle, the name of several places in various parts of France, of the same origin."]},{"name":"Fontenette","meanings":["French: topographic name from a diminutive of Old French <i>fontaine</i> ‘spring, well’ (see   Fontaine  ), or a habitational name from Fontenette, the name of several places mainly in the central part of France, of the same origin."]},{"name":"Fountain","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from one or more of the places in France named Fontaine, Fonteyne, or Lafontaine (see   Fontaine  ).","English: topographic name for someone who lived near a spring or well, from Middle English <i>fontayne</i> (Old French <i>fontaine</i>) ‘spring, fountain’, sometimes with a plural <i>-s</i>, and synonymous with   Well  , of which <i>Fountain(es)</i> may sometimes have been a translation."]},{"name":"Font","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Carlos, Juan, Luis, Miguel, Rafael, Eduardo, Raul, Eugenio, Pedro, Roberto, Aida.","Catalan and southern French: topographic name for someone living near a spring or well, Catalan and Occitan <i>font</i> ‘spring, well’ (from Latin <i>fons</i>, genitive <i>fontis</i>).","English: variant of   Fant  ."]},{"name":"Fontan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Angel, Benigno, Carlos, Jose, Juana, Manuel, Pedro, Adolfo, Aida, Alfredo, Candido, Emilia.","Spanish and Galician (<b>Fontán</b>): habitational name from any of the many places called Fontán, from <i>fontán</i> ‘spring’.","French: variant of   Fontaine  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aléaume de Fontaines was born in 1162, in Aberdeen, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Enguerraud Fontaines, was 24 and his mother, Cécily DE FONTAINES, was 37. He had at least 6 sons and 4 daughters with Laure DE SAINT-VALERY. He died in 1205, in Picardie, France, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1162–1205":"1162–1205","1160–1206":"1160–1206","1184–1238":"1184–1238","1190–1252":"1190–1252","–1164":"–1164","–1202":"–1202","–1214":"–1214","–1233":"–1233","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1138–1162":"1138–1162","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1190":"1190","1164":"1164","1252":"1252","1162":"1162","1184":"1184","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","alive 1164":"1164","1205":"1205","1238":"1238","1138":"1138","1214":"1214","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","1233":"1233","after 1202":"pärast 1202","Picardy, France":"Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Aberdeen, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeen, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","France":"Prantsusmaa","Aberdeen, Aberdeenshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni":"Aberdeen, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1162–1205":"1162–1205","1160–1206":"1160–1206","1184–1238":"1184–1238","1190–1252":"1190–1252","–1164":"–1164","–1202":"–1202","–1214":"–1214","–1233":"–1233","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1138–1162":"1138–1162","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1164":"1164","1252":"1252","1162":"1162","1184":"1184","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1206